#function to fill missing values
def fill_var(dataset):
        cat_var=dataset.select_dtypes(exclude=['number']).columns.tolist()
        num_var=dataset.select_dtypes(include=['number']).columns.tolist()
        for column in cat_var:
            dataset[column]=dataset[column].fillna(dataset[column].value_counts().index[0])
        for column in num_var:
            dataset[column]=dataset[column].fillna(dataset[column].mean())
        return dataset

def get_num_var(dataset):
    num_var=dataset.select_dtypes(include=['number'])
    return num_var

#function to count unique values of columns in categorical attributes, based on a primary column
def corr_counts(dataset, primary_column):
    var_counts=get_cat_var(dataset)
    for column in var_counts:
        result=dataset.groupby(primary_column)[column].value_counts()
        print(result)

corr_counts(dataset, 'location_region')

#function to normalize numerical values
def normalize_num_var(dataset):
    norm_num_var=get_num_var(dataset)
    for column in norm_num_var:
        result=(dataset[column]-dataset[column].min())/(dataset[column].max()-dataset[column].min())
        print(result)

#chart plotter function
def chart_plotter(dataset):
    columns_needed=get_cat_var(dataset)
    for column in columns_needed:
        x=dataset[column].unique()
        y=dataset[column].value_counts()
        fig_dims = (90, 90)
        fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=fig_dims)
        sns.set(font_scale=4)
        result=sns.barplot(x,y)
    
chart_plotter(dataset)

#calculating mean of all numerical values with numpy(imported as np)
def mean_calculator(dataset):
    num_var=get_num_var(dataset)
    for column in num_var:
        result=np.mean(dataset, axis=1)
    print(result)
